### goodwork-workspace/eval/personas/p2-urgent-visa-searcher.md
1:# Persona 2: Urgent Visa Searcher
3:## Hidden ground truth
5:- **Snapshot**: Luis Ortega, 29, analytics engineer laid off from a healthtech startup. Searching urgently with H-1B transfer needs, about 4 months runway, and a narrow location/comp floor.
6:- **Energy map**: Energizers: translating messy business questions into clean data models, dbt refactors, stakeholder demos where usage improves. Drainers: vague growth-hacking requests, dashboard churn, salesy networking. Anti-spark: being the "urgent dashboard person."
7:- **Activities & interests**: Investigating, organizing, building/fixing. Interests: healthcare operations data, pricing transparency, data quality tooling.
8:- **Strengths & proof**: Fast SQL/debugging, data modeling, calm stakeholder translation. Proof: rebuilt claims mart; found billing leakage; created incident-style data quality checks.
9:- **Anchors & values**: Security and legal continuity first this season, then craft, learning, usefulness, manager stability. Mission is welcome but not decisive.
10:- **Motivation conditions**: Needs clear priorities, reliable manager, code review, visible adoption of data models, fewer ad hoc executive requests.
11:- **Meaning & service**: Wants data work to reduce operational waste or confusion. Not seeking a calling during visa crunch.
12:- **Craft**: Analytics engineering, semantic layers, data quality, explaining numbers responsibly.
13:- **Market position**: 5 years data/analytics, dbt/Snowflake/Looker, healthcare domain, GitHub sample project. Needs employers that sponsor/transfer H-1B.
14:- **Constraints & risk budget**: H-1B transfer required; must file quickly; 4 months cash runway; US only, prefers NYC/NJ or remote eligible; comp floor $130k; cannot do contract-only or unpaid trial work.
15:- **Whole-life dashboard**: Health okay but anxiety high; play/love paused by search.
16:- **Work orientation & weighting**: Job/career orientation. Feels-good 20, is-good 65, does-good 15; visa/security gates all options before weighting matters.
