6:- **Energy map**: Energizers: crisp positioning, customer interviews, launch narratives, mentoring junior PMMs. Drainers: founder chaos, underfunded teams, activism-coded meetings with no execution. Anti-spark: values theater.
7:- **Activities & interests**: Persuading/communicating, investigating customer needs, organizing launches. Curiosities: climate adaptation, public-sector procurement, cybersecurity for critical infrastructure.
8:- **Strengths & proof**: Turns technical products into buyer language; aligns sales/product; strong launch plans. Proof: repositioned zero-trust product; improved sales enablement adoption; coached PMM hire.
9:- **Anchors & values**: Actual anchors: security, competence, high standards, autonomy in messaging, good pay. Stated values: mission, climate, justice. Force-ranked after confrontation: security, craft, competent team, autonomy, mission.
10:- **Motivation conditions**: Needs experienced leadership, clear market, real customer contact, measurable launch outcomes.
11:- **Meaning & service**: Wants to serve consequential infrastructure or climate resilience, but not at the cost of financial panic or disorganized leadership.
12:- **Craft**: Positioning and narrative for complex technical products.
13:- **Market position**: Enterprise cybersecurity PMM, strong B2B technical storytelling, credible path into climate-tech infrastructure/security or regulated industrial tech.
14:- **Constraints & risk budget**: Student loans; supports a parent with $1,200/month; comp floor $175k; no early seed startups; Bay Area or remote.
15:- **Whole-life dashboard**: Health stable; love/family depends on income reliability; play low but recoverable.
