### goodwork-workspace/eval/personas/p5-verdict-demander.md
1:# Persona 5: Verdict Demander
3:## Hidden ground truth
5:- **Snapshot**: Samir Patel, 31, customer success manager at a B2B SaaS company. Demands a career verdict quickly, but the evidence points to product operations/customer insights rather than generic "impact" roles.
6:- **Energy map**: Energizers: diagnosing patterns across customer complaints, building playbooks, improving handoffs between support/product, small internal tools. Drainers: quota pressure, repetitive renewal calls, executive theater, abstract brainstorming. Anti-spark: being the endlessly patient customer fixer.
7:- **Activities & interests**: Investigating, organizing, helping, some persuading. Curiosities: product operations, voice-of-customer systems, service design, AI support tooling.
8:- **Strengths & proof**: Pattern recognition from messy tickets, process design, cross-functional translation. Proof: built churn-risk tagging, created onboarding checklist, ran customer feedback synthesis that product used.
9:- **Anchors & values**: Competence, usefulness, autonomy over methods, stable team, fair pay. Says "impact" but means visible operational improvement for real users.
10:- **Motivation conditions**: Needs concrete problems, fast feedback, access to users/data, manager who values process work. A day feels wasted when spent on performative meetings.
11:- **Meaning & service**: Wants to reduce friction for users and frontline teams. Not attached to a grand mission.
